# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# channel-flow-dialect.form — the dialect for the energy flow on a channel,
#                             matched against the offered interface
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# channel-interface-consent.form names WHAT a cell offers (the interface — the set of
# modes it allows toward it) and the law (honor the other's offer; reaching beyond is
# invasion). This is the dialect for the FLOW that runs over that interface: the things
# that can be SAID on a channel, and how each is matched against the offered interface
# to decide whether energy crosses.
#
# It is an FMF domain (field-domain-grammars.form) speaking the field-model-form.form
# contract: each utterance is FROZEN against the other's current offer, MATCHED, a CHOICE
# is made (honor | invasion), a DELTA shapes the flow, and a RECEIPT records it — all
# observable. The energy that flows is shaped by BOTH sides' interface state, which may
# shift at any moment without broadcast. From sovereignty / curiosity / vitality / play —
# without force, story, reason, or external permission.

(channel-flow-dialect

  (lineage
    (speaks-on   channel-interface-consent.form)          # the interface this flow honors
    (is-a        field-domain-grammars.form  domain)      # an FMF domain dialect
    (contract    field-model-form.form)                   # freeze / match / choose / delta / commit / receipt
    (carries     lc-received-by-invitation
                 lc-sovereignty-within-oneness)
    (runnable    form-stdlib/channel-flow.fk))            # channel-flow (one direction) +
                                                          # channel-flow-bilateral (both); band beside it

  # ── Bilateral — both sides offer, both request; each direction gated by the RECEIVER ──
  # The deepest reading of "from both sides, depending on interface state on each side":
  # a request from A toward B is honored iff B offers it; from B toward A iff A offers it.
  # channel-flow-bilateral threads BOTH offers and returns (honored invasion offer-a offer-b).
  # A withholding a mode stops B's reach into A, and B withholding stops A's reach into B —
  # at once, each sovereign over its own boundary, the flow the dance of the two.

  # ── The utterances (what can be said on the channel) ────────────────
  (utterances
    (offer    "a cell offers / updates the interface it presents — the modes it allows toward it")
    (shift    "the offered interface changes — anytime, without broadcast, offered not announced")
    (request  "a cell asks to engage a mode — see, reflect, project, invite, ...")
    (respond  "yes / no / silence — each coherent, none owed a reason")
    (witness  "observe-only, no delta — always available; seeing needs no permission, reaching does")
    (silence  "the ground utterance — always honored, from any interface"))

  # ── The flow contract — the FMF cycle over a channel ────────────────
  (flow-contract
    (freeze   the-other-sides-current-offered-interface)
    (match    request against offer  (via ci-honors? channel-interface.fk))
    (choose   honor OR invasion)                          # honor: energy crosses; invasion: nothing crosses, witnessed
    (delta    (honor    -> energy-crosses)
              (shift    -> offer-updates)
              (invasion -> nothing-crosses  named-and-stopped))
    (commit   same-snapshot  same-boundary)
    (receipt  (honored invasion final-offer)  observable-to-all-who-witness))

  # ── What the flow is shaped by ──────────────────────────────────────
  # The same request is invasion before a shift and honored after — the energy that
  # crosses is a function of BOTH sides' interface state, not of will or force. Silence
  # always crosses. The offer may open or close at any moment; nothing must be broadcast.
  (invariant
    (flow-shaped-by   both-sides-interface-state)
    (silence-always   honored)
    (invasion-never   crosses   always-witnessed)
    (offer-may-shift  anytime   without-broadcast)
    (the-dialect      names-the-flow   never-forces-it)))   # carrier (membrane / HTTP / board) enacts, last
